# Local secrets for live cloud integration testing against real (non-emulated) storage.
# Copy to .env (already gitignored) and fill in real values -- never commit real credentials.
#
# docker compose auto-loads .env at the repo root for ${VAR} substitution in
# docker-compose.yml; nothing else needs to change to pick these up.

# --- Live AWS S3 (see docker-compose.yml's python-test-s3-live service, TESTING.md's
#     "Live AWS S3 (real bucket, not MinIO)" section) ---------------------------------------
# IAM user access key with the least-privilege policy documented in TESTING.md, scoped to
# this bucket only (s3:ListBucket, s3:GetBucketLocation, s3:GetObject, s3:PutObject).
# The real bucket name is deliberately not in this checked-in template -- fill it in below,
# in your local .env only.
S3_BUCKET=
AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=
AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=
# Required in practice: the bucket's actual region. A region mismatch here surfaces as a
# confusing NoSuchBucket error (S3 rejects a region-specific-endpoint request for a bucket
# that lives elsewhere rather than redirecting), not an auth/permissions error.
AWS_DEFAULT_REGION=
